    Introduction to tablestylizer

    Example Dataset with Imaginary Demographic Data for Practicing with the tablestylizer Package

    tablestylizer_df.Rd

    This dataset provides an example of fictional data related to a group of individuals. It includes information such as age, sex, height, coffee preferences, favorite color, and group affiliation.

    Usage

    tablestylizer_df

    Format

    A tibble with 20 rows and 7 variables:

    ID

    Unique identifier for each individual.

    Age (years)

    Age of the individuals in years.

    Women

    Indicates whether the individual is female (Yes) or not (No).

    Height (inches)

    Height of the individuals in inches.

    Likes coffee

    Individuals' preference for coffee (Yes or No).

    Favorite color

    Favorite color of the individuals (Red, Green, or Blue).

    Group

    Group affiliation of the individuals (A, B, or C).

    Source

    This data is generated for the purpose of illustrating data manipulation and analysis in R. It does not represent real-world individuals or situations.

    Examples

    head(tablestylizer_df)
#> # A tibble: 6 × 7
#>   ID    `Age (years)` Women `Height (inches)` `Likes coffee` `Favorite color`
#>   <chr>         <int> <fct>             <dbl> <fct>          <fct>           
#> 1 01               41 Yes                  67 No             Blue            
#> 2 02               18 Yes                  67 No             Blue            
#> 3 03               21 Yes                  67 No             Green           
#> 4 04               73 Yes                  65 No             Red             
#> 5 05               43 No                   69 No             Red             
#> 6 06               70 Yes                  66 Yes            Green           
#> # ℹ 1 more variable: Group <fct>
